---Query a: How many check-ins were done in the different New York neighborhoods in the last 10 minutes, divided by category?CREATE VIEW nyc.view_a WITH (sw = '10 minute') AS  SELECT userid, avenueid, avenuecategory, points_avenue, time_timestamp  FROM nyc.stream_checkins;CREATE VIEW query_a AS (    WITH cv_window AS (     SELECT COUNT(*), avenuecategory, nyc.neighborhoods.boroname FROM nyc.stream_checkins, nyc.neighborhoods WHERE ST_CONTAINS(ST_SetSRID((points_avenue), nyc.neighborhoods.geometry) GROUP BY avenuecategory    ));
SELECT s.userid, s.venuecategory, s.points_avenueFROM nyc.neighborhoods AS nJOIN nyc.view_a AS sON ST_Contains(n.geom, s.points_avenue)WHERE n.boroname = 'Brooklyn'order by s.userid;

CREATE VIEW query_a AS (WITH VIEW cv_window AS (    SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER n.boroname));CREATE VIEW query_a AS (WITH VIEW cv_window AS (    SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER n.boroname));

CREATE VIEW query_a AS (WITH VIEW cv_window AS (    SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER n.boroname));

CREATE VIEW nyc.view_a WITH (sw = '10 minute') AS  SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER BY n.boroname

---Query a: How many check-ins were done in the different New York neighborhoods in the last 10 minutes, divided by category?CREATE VIEW nyc.view_a WITH (sw = '10 minute') AS  SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.stream_checkins AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER BY n.boroname

---Query a: How many check-ins were done in the different New York neighborhoods in the last 10 minutes, divided by category?CREATE VIEW nyc.view_a WITH (sw = '10 minute') AS  SELECT userid, avenueid, avenuecategory, points_avenue, time_timestamp  FROM nyc.stream_checkins;SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER BY n.boroname
SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    ORDER BY n.boroname, s.avenuecategory, n.boroname

SELECT COUNT(*), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    ORDER BY n.boroname
SELECT COUNT(n), s.avenuecategory, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY s.avenuecategory    ORDER BY s.avenuecategory

SELECT DISTINCT s.avenuecategory, n.boroname,COUNT((n.boroname ))FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)GROUP BY s.avenuecategory, n.boronameORDER BY s.avenuecategory

---Query b: What were the check-ins made within a radius of 300 meters from the "Broad St" stop in the last 20 minutes?CREATE VIEW nyc.view_b WITH (sw = '20 minute') AS  SELECT userid, avenueid, avenuecategory, points_avenue, time_timestamp  FROM nyc.stream_checkins;SELECT *FROM nyc.view_b AS vi JOIN nyc.subway_station AS sub    ON ST_DWithin(vi.geom, sub.geom, 300)    WHERE sub.name='Broad St'

SELECT vi.userid, vi.avenueid, vi.avenuecategory, vi.points_avenue, vi.time_timestampFROM nyc.view_b AS vi JOIN nyc.subway_stations AS sub    ON ST_DWithin(vi.points_avenue, sub.geom, 300)    WHERE sub.name='Broad St'

SELECT COUNT(s)/ST_AREA(n.geom)/ 1000000.0 AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (n.boroname)

SELECT (COUNT(s.avenueid)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0 AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (n.boroname)

SELECT ((COUNT(s.avenueid)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0) AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname)SELECT ((COUNT(s.avenueid)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0) AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname)

SELECT ((COUNT(s.avenueid)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0) AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (check_in_density_per_square_kilometer, n.boroname)

SELECT n.boroname, ((COUNT(s.avenueid)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0) AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (n.boroname)

SELECT n.boroname, DISTINCT ((COUNT(s)/ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0) AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometer    FROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)    GROUP BY (n.boroname)

SELECT n.boroname, count (s.userid)/(ST_AREA(n.geom))/1000000.0 AS check_in_density_per_square_kilometerFROM nyc.neighborhoods AS n JOIN nyc.view_a AS s ON ST_CONTAINS(n.geom, s.points_avenue)GROUP BY (n.boroname),n.geom having (count (n.boroname) <=1)

from kafka import KafkaConsumerfrom json import loadsimport psycopg2import timeimport randomconsumer = KafkaConsumer(    'acme',     bootstrap_servers=['192.168.0.1:9092'],     auto_offset_reset='earliest',     enable_auto_commit=True,     group_id='my-group',     value_deserializer=lambda x: loads(x.decode('utf-8')))conn = psycopg2.connect('dbname=postgres user=postgres host=localhost port=5432 password=postgres')pipeline = conn.cursor()create_stream = """CREATE FOREIGN TABLE stream_acme8 (company text, time_timestamp date, quote numeric(7,2)) SERVER pipelinedb"""pipeline.execute(create_stream)create_cv = """CREATE VIEW continuous_acme8 WITH (action= materialize) AS SELECT company, time_timestamp, quote FROM stream_acme """pipeline.execute(create_cv)conn.commit()for message in consumer:    message = message.value    quote=message.get('quote')    timestamp=message.get('timestamp')    company= message.get('company')    pipeline.execute("INSERT INTO stream_acme8 (company, time_timestamp, quote) VALUES ('"+str(company)+"',to_timestamp("+str(timestamp)+"),"+str(quote)+")")    print('Message {} '.format(message))    time.sleep(0.01)pipeline.execute('DROP VIEW continuous_acme8')pipeline.execute('DROP FOREIGN TABLE stream_acme8')conn.commit()pipeline.close()

Le differenze sostanziali tra IPv4 e IPv6 sono:1. Nell' IPv6 non esiste un campo opzioni ma vi è un puntatore ad esse chiamato "next header" che indica le opzioni che arricchiscono il pacchetto, come l'aggiunta di un livello di sicurezza maggiore, un percorso segnato da determinati router o da determinate linee ecc.2. Nell'IPv4 i campi source e destination sono composti da 32 bit mentre nell'IPv6 sono composti da 16byte.3. Gli indirizzi IPv6 sono numeri binari rappresentati in esadecimale, divisi da ":" e lo zero si può indicare con "::"Gli indirizzi IPv4 sono numeri binari rappresentati in decimale con rappresentazione puntata.

In particolare, una funzione hash nel random oracle model deve soddisfare la seguente proprietà: se ho calcolato h(x) per un insieme di messaggi M, allora fissato un message digest y e un messaggio x’, la probabilità Pr(h(x)=y) non dipende dalla cardinalità di un M.

I record dei pazienti diabetici sono stati ottenuti da due fonti: un dispositivo di registrazione elettronica automatico e documenti cartacei. Il dispositivo automatico aveva un orologio interno per timestamp eventi, mentre i record di carta solo fornito "orari logici" slot (colazione, pranzo, cena, prima di coricarsi). Per i registri cartacei, i tempi fissi sono stati assegnati a colazione (08:00), pranzo (12:00), cena (18:00) e ora di andare a letto (22:00). Pertanto, i registri cartacei hanno tempi di registrazione fittizi e uniformi, mentre i registri elettronici hanno timbri più realistici.+

dato un set di segmenti appartenenti a un poligono convessola struttura del segmento sarà composta da 2 punti, ordiniamo casualmente i punti come P1 e P2 i punti vengono composti da x e y.ordiniamo in un array i segmenti per P1 per x inserendoli in un array (first), nel caso della la x corrisponda a un secondo segmento verrano ordinati in ordine lessicograficoordiniamo in un secondo array i segmenti per P2 ripetendo la stessa cosa avvenuta per il primo arrayqueste 2 azioni hanno tutte e 2 O(n log(n))Ora prendiamo il primo segmento nell'array first e cerchiamo il suo successore sia nel primo che nel secondo array dove il secondo punto del segmento corrisponde al primo punto di uno dei segmenti che si trovano nei 2 arrayQuesta azione richiede O (log (n)) ma avvendo sempre n-1 segmenti dato lo scorrere della lista otteniamo O (n log(n))
